features: 『Solution』Providing a convenient solution for extending the connection from power supply to motherboard（Note: It doesn't work with graphic card）;

『CPU 8P(4+4) M-FM』Connector A: ATX 12V 8 pin (4+4) male (Detachable CPU 8 pin(4+4) end could be used as EPS ATX 8 pin or P4 ATX 4 pin by sliding on/off the 4 pin.), connector B: ATX 12V 8 pin female ( NOTE: it is CPU 8 pin, not pci-e 8 pin);

『Compatibility』Compatible with power supplies with ATX 8 pin male port output & motherboards with ATX 4 pin or ATX 8 pin port; (This cable is a common power supply extension cable, not converted cable. It supports all of power supplies with CPU 8 pin male port output.)
『Parameter』Length(including connectors):9.5-inch(24cm), Gauge: 1007-18AWG(standard tin-coating copper wire), Max power rating: 400W, Quantity: 2pcs, Self-adhesive tape*1pcs;

『Note』This cable is a common power supply extension cable, not converted cable. It does not work with GPU. If you use it to connect your GPU, it will definitely burn or damage the GPU and we won’t take any responsibility for wrongly using or installing. Please carefully check the compatible types or contact us if you are not sure if it supports your power supply;
body.description: Features: The COMeap ATX 8 Pin male to female cable is to provide a convenient solution for extending the connection from power supply to motherboard; Support: Compatible with power supplies with ATX 8 pin male port output & motherboards with ATX 4 pin or ATX 8 pin port; (This cable is a common power supply extension cable, not converted cable. It supports all of power supplies with CPU 8 pin male port output.) Specification: Length(including connectors): 9.5-inch(24cm) Connectors: 1x ATX 8pin (4+4) male, 1x ATX 8 pin female Gauge: 1007-18AWG(standard tin-coating copper wire) Including: ATX 8 Pin male to female cable*2pcs; Self-adhesive tape*1pcs; Note: 1. This cable was only designed to extend the length of ATX 8 pin power supply cable for better cable management; 2. Both of connectors are ATX 8 pin, not pci-e 8 pin;

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality, works as expected.
reviews.reviewText: Good product. Cables feel durable, they should last a long time. I wasn't sure what to expect with this bargain find but I'm really glad I took the chance. We recently got a new computer case whose PSU compartment is too far away for the CPU2 power cable to reach. This fixed us right up, with a few inches to spare.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are awesome.
reviews.reviewText: I bought a 850 watt PC modular PC power supply, but the two cables that came with it were about 3 inches too short to get all the way up to the top left corner of the motherboard for the CPU power. While I could have probably made it work, I didn't like the strain it was putting on the wires, so I just bought these extension cables instead. They fit perfectly and are well built.

reviews.reviewText: These should come standard with motherboards. Good product, works great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These cables are to extend the length of your power supply's provided atx CPU power cables. IT DOES NOT REPLACE THE CABLES PROVIDED BY YOUR PSU. Using psu cables not provided by your psu manufacturer can cause irreversible damage. Use these to extend not replace. This is a generic cable, and can extend any 2 x 4 atx cpu power cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does the job.
reviews.reviewText: It may not be a fancy braided cable extension, however it does the job just fine. I needed one of these because my mother's PC case just barely fits an ATX board even though it is advertised as an ATX mid-tower case. Since the ATX board covered some of the cable-routing holes, I had to get a bit creative with cable management. The EPS cable on the PSU was not long enough to reach the motherboard's connector once I did my routing. This did the job perfectly.
Just a nice little extension for my build, did the job perfectly and still using to this day
